subSubSection.paragraph:
Anterior dorsal margin of first chaetiger papillose. Chaetigers 1–3 of similar length. Chaetal transition from cephalic cage to body chaetae abrupt; anchylosed, falcate blunt neurohooks start from chaetiger 4 (aristate neurohooks in some 
paratypes
). Gonopodial lobes not seen (even in specimens without tunic).
